Program: Discovery
Title: The demise of the big animals
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry3l
Last Broadcast Date: 24 May 2002
What caused the extinction of some of the world's largest mammals, some 15,000 years ago? Around this time there was a profusion of big animals or megafauna on the Earth. Super-sized kangaroos, bears and cats lived throughout the planet, but within a few hundred years these animals were extinct. Could it have been by disease? Show less